President Muhammadu Buhari has mourned the former Secretary to the Federal Government, Chief Ufot Ekaette. Buhari, in a statement yesterday by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity Garba Shehu, expressed shock and grief over the death of Ekaette, whom he described as “a consummate administrator who dedicated himself to duty in the course of his distinguished public service.”  Former SGF, Ufot Ekaette, dies at 80, as Buhari mourns N’Delta group threatens mass action over Reps’ attack on Ekaette Buhari yet to make appointments, 2 weeks after OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY